<TITLE> Thai court frees ex-PM Thaksin on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bangkok, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Thailand's Supreme Court freed former Prime Minister Thaksin Shinawatra on bail on Thursday and said he could travel overseas but had to seek permission first. The court freed Thaksin on 8-million-baht ($268,500) bail and set March 12 as the start of his trial on a corruption charge relating to his wife's purchase of a prime piece of Bangkok real estate while in office, it said in a statement. ($1=29.80 baht)
